# migrated from tests/cases/reflexive_selftest.chat (hermetic + isolated, perf-held)
[mock hermetic]
!set PARROT0_BASE=
!set PARROT0_SESSION=
!set PARROT0_WORLD_FACTS=0
!set PARROT0_LANG=en
!reset

[test reflexive_selftest]
!timeout 0
# gen167/168 (E1 reflexive, capstone): parrot0 RUNS its own composition. Asked to
# prove its parts compose by running it itself, it spins up a fresh copy of itself
# (brain_create), generates a held-out dialogue (gen168: fresh vocab per run) over
# the parts derived from its module(X) self-model, runs it through brain_respond,
# and reports the verdict + the cooperation it actually OBSERVED — computed from
# real output, not a canned string. Footprint-free; touches no files, commits
# nothing (anti-self-management). This is the first self-test of a fresh session,
# so it uses the first vocab tuple deterministically.
> prove your parts compose by running it yourself
< I ran it on a fresh copy of myself with held-out names (a brave knight named aldric): knowledge, abduce and robust — 3 of 3 parts fired and cooperated. Observed: My conclusion that aldric is a hero rests on 2 load-bearing facts: knight(aldric), brave(aldric). Removing any one would overturn it. Composition holds (PASS). No file was touched; an external agent still owns edits and commits.
